  {
   "kind": "heading",
   "level": 2,
   "text": "Additional Notes on Anode Mixing"
  },
  {
   "kind": "bullets",
   "items": [
    "Viscosity is the primary metric to achieve within target value.",
    "When adding powder, ramp up agitation speed from the lowest setting (5/100 rpm) and increase in 2 to 5 or 100 rpm increments until all loose powder is incorporated. Start with Dispersion blade. Scrape the agitation blades after every powder addition step (i.e. graphite, Super-P).",
    "Pay close attention to the slurry temperature - very important for meeting the viscosity target consistently.",
    "Make sure the chiller is always connected to the main tank and running.",
    "Viscosity can increase after degassing step.",
    "For other troubleshooting, refer to the \"OCAP\" tab."
   ]
  },
  {
   "kind": "heading",
   "level": 2,
   "text": "Anode Recipe Steps - Single Vessel Mix"
