  {
   "kind": "heading",
   "level": 2,
   "text": "Note on Anode Press/Slit maintenance"
  },
  {
   "kind": "bullets",
   "items": [
    "Every 300-500 meters, wipe the main roll and nip rolls with water then acetone on cleanroom wipes (anti-dust/static).",
    "Anode main roll is equipped with a cleaning mechanism (scraper); however, this doesn't work very well and requires manual cleaning.",
    "Guide roll (press + slit) needs cleaning about once a week.",
    "Change the rolls as needed (defect or damage) and equip with spares.",
    "Knife maintenance: replace when there is a chip or breakage."
   ]
  },
